{%- comment -%}

  Assigns default variables for the provided context so you don't have have to. In your schema, if you set the `id` property to one of the following values below, it will be automatically available to you in the given context:

  Context: 'section'
  - blocks
  - enabled
  - children_classes
  - is_slider
  - heading
  - heading_classes
  - sub_heading
  - sub_heading_classes
  - button_one_text
  - button_one_href
  - button_one_classes
  - button_two_text
  - button_two_href
  - button_two_classes
  - content
  - limit

  Context: 'block'
  -

  You can overwrite these default values by passing in an argument of the same name:

  e.g.

  {%- include 'section',
    section_snippet: 'row-case-statement',
    blocks: instagram_array,
    sub_heading: 'Shop Instagram' -%}


{%- endcomment -%}


